You can get an **iOS 26–style** feel in Flutter on **both** iOS and Android while keeping **one UzaPoint palette** shared with `Frontend_Web`. The trick is: **same brand tokens everywhere**, **platform-native motion and chrome where it helps**, and **POS-safe surfaces** where glass and blur would hurt readability.

