## 3. Flutter strategy: one design system, two platform personalities

```mermaid
flowchart TB
Tokens[Shared UzaPoint tokens]
Tokens --> Core[Core widgets: UButton, UCard, UListTile]
Core --> Adaptive[Adaptive shell]
Adaptive --> iOS[iOS 26-inspired: glass nav, Cupertino sheets]
Adaptive --> Android[M3 expressive: tonal surfaces, predictive back]
```

| Layer | Responsibility |
|-------|----------------|
| **Tokens** | Colors, radii, spacing, typography, elevation, motion durations |
| **Core components** | Same API on both OSes; look 95% identical |
| **Adaptive shell** | Tab bar behavior, back gesture, status bar, haptics |
| **Platform polish** | iOS: glass blur, live activities later; Android: dynamic color optional OFF to protect brand |

Use Flutter’s **adaptive** patterns conceptually:

- `TargetPlatform.iOS` → glass tab bar, Cupertino date picker, edge swipe back  
- `TargetPlatform.android` → Material bottom nav, ripple where appropriate, predictive back  

**Do not** run two completely different apps — cashiers should recognize UzaPoint instantly vs web dashboard.

