## 4. Mapping iOS 26 features → your screen map

### Global shell (all logged-in screens)

| iOS 26 feature | Flutter approach | UzaPoint use |
|----------------|------------------|--------------|
| Liquid Glass tab bar | `BackdropFilter` + semi-transparent bar; `NavigationBar` custom | Home / POS / Inventory / More |
| Bar minimizes on scroll | `NestedScrollView` + `SliverAppBar` | Dashboard, inventory list |
| Edge-to-edge content | `SafeArea` only where needed; list under glass bar | Analytics, sales history |
| Large title → inline title | Collapsing header | “Inventory”, “Payments” |

**POS tab exception:** Center **POS** tab — larger icon, solid or lightly glass **primary** pill; always visible (no hide-on-scroll on POS root).

### Authentication & onboarding

| Screen | iOS 26 style | Palette rule |
|--------|--------------|--------------|
| Splash | Subtle glass logo plate on `background` | “U” = `foreground` on `primary` or inverted |
| Welcome | Full-bleed soft gradient using `muted` only — **no new brand colors** | |
| Login / Sign up | Frosted card on `card` + `border` | Primary button = web `primary` |
| Biometric | System UI; your frame uses `card` | |

### Dashboard (3.x)

- Metric cards: **solid `card`**, light shadow — not glass (read numbers fast).  
- Charts: **`chart-1`–`chart-5`** exactly as web.  
- Quick actions: glass **chips** OK for decoration; labels on solid fill.

### POS (4.x) — special rules

| Screen | Style |
|--------|--------|
| POS main | Solid `background`; category chips `secondary`; selected = `primary` |
| Cart / Checkout | **Opaque** panels — prices and Pay CTA must pass WCAG contrast |
| Payment processing | Glass overlay OK on dimmed scrim |
| Receipt | Paper-like `card` (white/black), monospace totals optional |
| Scanner | Full-screen camera; UI chrome glass **top/bottom only** |
| Offline banner | `destructive` or amber semantic — define `warning` token if web adds it later |

**Rule:** Glass for **chrome**, solid for **money and SKUs**.

### Inventory, sales, payments, analytics, reports

- Lists: edge-to-edge rows, `border` separators, swipe actions (iOS) / swipe + long-press (Android).  
- Detail screens: hero product name + solid info sections.  
- Filters: **bottom sheet** with glass handle (iOS 26 sheet style) — shared on both platforms via `showModalBottomSheet` styling.

### Settings (11.x)

- Grouped list like iOS Settings — matches web tabs (Business, Payment, Notifications, Account).  
- Toggles: platform switch with **tint = `primary`**.  
- Destructive rows: `destructive` only.

